object.script:
function onTick() is_buyer = property.getBool("is_buyer") is_fluid = property.getBool("is_fluid") resource = property.getText("resource") if is_buyer then resource = resource .. " buyer" else resource = resource .. " seller" end price = input.getNumber(1) is_clogged = input.getBool(1) is_pumping = input.getBool(2) end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(128, 128, 128)
screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, resource, 0, -1)
if is_buyer then screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, "Buy price:", -1, 0) -- Sell here for! else screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, "Sell price:", -1, 0) -- Buy here for! end
screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, "$" .. string.format("%.3f", price), 1, 0)
if is_clogged then screen.setColor(255, 16, 0) screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, "Filter is clogged!", 0, 1) -- draw glowing/blinking warning sign elseif is_pumping then screen.setColor(96, 96, 0) if is_buyer then if is_fluid then screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, "Pumping IN", 0, 1) -- draw animated pump up arrow icon else screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, "Loading", 0, 1) -- not needed as hoppers will always buy! end else if is_fluid then screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, "Pumping OUT", 0, 1) -- draw animated pump down arrow icon else screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, "Loading", 0, 1) -- draw animated coal pouring icon end end else screen.setColor(64, 255, 0) screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, "Ready", 0, 1) end
end
